+# Briefing Logic V2 Final Review Fixes Design
+
+## Goal
+
+Close the remaining fail-open paths in weekly leadership caches, source-universe refreshes, earnings verification, and business directness while preserving the existing feature-branch automation contract.
+
+## Architecture
+
+`weekly_universe_cache.py` owns the shared weekly snapshot constants and validation contract. KR and US leadership resolvers call it before labeling any cache fresh. A snapshot is fresh only when its scope, schema, timestamp, symbol counts, coverage values, and required-source provenance all validate.
+
+`full_market_scan.py` attaches explicit source provenance to each loaded universe. KR requires successful KOSPI and KOSDAQ coverage from KRX. US requires successful NASDAQ-listed and other-listed endpoint coverage, with exchange counts retained as provenance. `scripts/refresh_weekly_universe.py` rejects missing or failed required sources before liquidity processing.
+
+Weekly publishing is a small file transaction. Dated CSV, current CSV, and watchlist are written to temporary files and validated first. Publish order is dated, watchlist, then current; current is the final commit marker. Existing files are backed up and restored on any publish failure, and temporary files are always cleaned.
+
+Business classification separates primary evidence (`industry`, structured business tags, and business descriptions) from auxiliary labels (`sector`, `sector_detail`, `sector_theme_group`, and `theme_hint`). Auxiliary-only matches cannot be direct. Earnings verification rejects future releases and invalid quarter-release-source linkage.
+
+## Failure Policy
+
+- Missing, malformed, future, stale, or internally inconsistent weekly metadata cannot produce `weekly_liquid_full_market_fresh`.
+- Missing source provenance or any failed required source preserves the prior current cache and watchlist.
+- Future or disconnected earnings metadata produces `distorted_or_missing` and `earnings_verified=False`.
+- Theme-only business evidence is observation-only and requires sector review.
+- Practical outputs are selected only through `canonical_practical_candidates`; observations never backfill Top lists.
+
+## Verification
+
+Unit tests cover all negative boundaries and source-partial failures. A frozen positive fixture covers one practical candidate through enrichment and verifies identical ordering across Markdown, Telegram Top, and TradingView main outputs, plus disjoint observation files and zero-candidate behavior.
+
+No changes are made to `main`, cron, Telegram/Drive configuration, `.env`, credentials, or operational result files.
